[5
Date: 4 Oct 2000 06:49:17 +0200
From: Andy Main <andymain@aucegypt.edu>

Chicken Color Hypothesis
-------------------------
The hypothesis that chickens do not make good sentinels because of their
color needs further investigation. This would mean a difference between
_Culex_ transmitting West Nile virus and _Culiseta_ or _ Culex_
transmitting Eastern equine encephalitis virus or Western equine
encephalitis virus, respectively. Having had no experience with sentinel
chickens and St Louis encephalitis virus, I would be interested in comments
from those who have.
This year in Connecticut, we found West Nile virus antibody in white geese
at the same place we tested chickens of many different colors and did not
find antibody.
--
Andy Main
Chair, Biology Department
The American University in Cairo
<andymain@aucegypt.edu>
